1.  Compute \(AB\).  
    A = \(\begin{pmatrix}1&2\\3&4\end{pmatrix},\)
    B = \(\begin{pmatrix}-2&1\\\tfrac32&-\tfrac12\end{pmatrix}.\)

    \(AB = 
      \begin{pmatrix}1&2\\3&4\end{pmatrix}
      \begin{pmatrix}-2&1\\\tfrac32&-\tfrac12\end{pmatrix}
      = \begin{pmatrix}
          1\cdot(-2) + 2\cdot\tfrac32 & 1\cdot1 + 2\cdot\bigl(-\tfrac12\bigr)\\
          3\cdot(-2) + 4\cdot\tfrac32 & 3\cdot1 + 4\cdot\bigl(-\tfrac12\bigr)
        \end{pmatrix}\)

    = \(\begin{pmatrix}
          -2 + 3 & 1 - 1\\
          -6 + 6 & 3 - 2
       \end{pmatrix}
      = \begin{pmatrix}1&0\\0&1\end{pmatrix} = I.\)

2.  Compute \(BA\):

    \(BA = 
      \begin{pmatrix}-2&1\\\tfrac32&-\tfrac12\end{pmatrix}
      \begin{pmatrix}1&2\\3&4\end{pmatrix}
      = \begin{pmatrix}
          -2\cdot1 + 1\cdot3 & -2\cdot2 + 1\cdot4\\
          \tfrac32\cdot1 + \bigl(-\tfrac12\bigr)\cdot3 
            & \tfrac32\cdot2 + \bigl(-\tfrac12\bigr)\cdot4
        \end{pmatrix}\)

    = \(\begin{pmatrix}
          -2 + 3 & -4 + 4\\
          \tfrac32 - \tfrac32 & 3 - 2
       \end{pmatrix}
      = \begin{pmatrix}1&0\\0&1\end{pmatrix} = I.\)

Since \(AB = BA = I\), \(A\) and \(B\) are indeed inverses of each other.

